# ClearAI Frontend — environment variables
#
# After the MSAL.js cutover (2026-05-05), the SPA talks directly to
# APIM with a USER-issued Entra access token (Authorization Code +
# PKCE via @azure/msal-browser). The previous SWA-managed-Functions
# BFF in clearai-frontend/api/ is dead and will be deleted by infra
# in a follow-up.
#
# Build-time vars (PUBLIC_*) below are NOT secrets — they get inlined
# into the bundle and into network responses anyone can read. Only
# put public discovery values here. The four PUBLIC_ENTRA_* + the
# PUBLIC_APIM_BASE_URL match what's set in the SWA's app settings
# blade for the deployed environment; for local dev copy this file
# to .env and fill in the same values.

# Tenant your users sign in against. The Infinite Apps tenant.
PUBLIC_ENTRA_TENANT_ID=<your-tenant-guid>

# Public client ID of the SPA app reg (ClearAI SPA DEV). NOT a secret —
# the OAuth spec assumes it's public.
PUBLIC_ENTRA_CLIENT_ID=<your-spa-client-id-guid>

# Delegated scope MSAL requests on the user's behalf. Must match the
# `access_as_user` scope exposed by the API's app reg.
PUBLIC_ENTRA_API_SCOPE=api://<your-api-app-id-guid>/access_as_user

# APIM hostname the browser calls directly. CORS allow-list on APIM
# must include http://localhost:4321 (and 5180) for local dev.
PUBLIC_APIM_BASE_URL=https://<your-apim-host>.azure-api.net
